title: ICE: op.layout.ty.is_simd()

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code `cargo new` and put the code into `src/main.rs` Then run `cargo check --all-targets` ```Rust #![feature(platform_intrinsics)] #![feature(staged_api)] struct f32x3(); extern "platform-intrinsic" { #[rustc_const_stable(feature = "foo", since = "1.3.37")] fn simd_extract(x: T, idx: u32) -> U; } const Y0: i8 = unsafe { simd_extract(f32x3, 0) }; fn main() {} ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.67.0-nightly (a28f3c88e 2022-11-20) binary: rustc commit-hash: a28f3c88e50a77bc2a91889241248c4543854e61 commit-date: 2022-11-20 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.67.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.4 ``` ### Error output ``` warning: type `f32x3` should have an upper camel case name --> src/main.rs:3:8 | 3 | struct f32x3(); | ^^^^^ help: convert the identifier to upper camel case (notice the capitalization): `F32x3` | = note: `#[warn(non_camel_case_types)]` on by default warning: struct `f32x3` is never constructed --> src/main.rs:3:8 | 3 | struct f32x3(); | ^^^^^ | = note: `#[warn(dead_code)]` on by default warning: constant `Y0` is never used --> src/main.rs:8:7 | 8 | const Y0: i8 = unsafe { simd_extract(f32x3, 0) }; | ^^ warning: function `simd_extract` is never used --> src/main.rs:6:8 | 6 | fn simd_extract(x: T, idx: u32) -> U; | ^^^^^^^^^^^^ ```
